Headquarters Regions: Greater Minneapolis-Saint Paul Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Enstratius(Formerly Enstratus) provides cloud infrastructure management for public, private, and hybrid cloud operations aligned with enterprise governance and security needs. Enstratius provides users with a single access-controlled view across all corporate cloud resources. Users with the appropriate access rights may directly provision virtual machines across multiple clouds or they can deploy fully-automated applications from a cloud-independent service catalog. Features of Enstratius include: self-service provisioning/de-provisioning of cloud resources, multi-currency cost/chargeback tracking, customizable role-based access controls, single login to manage all cloud resources, support for enterprise authentication systems including SAML 2.0 and OpenID, automated encryption of all cloud data in transit and at rest with all keys stored outside of the cloud, full application automation including auto-scaling, auto-recovery, cloud bursting, and disaster recovery, and a service catalog of pre-configured applications with the ability to publish your own. Enstratius supports the following public clouds: Amazon Web Services, AT&T Synaptic Storage, Bluelock, Cloud Central, CloudSigma, GoGrid, Google Storage, IBM, Microsoft Azure Storage, NTT, Rackspace, and Terremark. Enstratius supports the following private cloud platforms: Atmos Storage, Citrix/Cloud.com, [Eucalyptus], [Nimbula], OpenStack, and Zimory.

Description: The MCC Group has been a pioneer in providing customers complete solutions to their building needs for over 50 years
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: The MCC Group, founded in 1958, is a complete M.E.P. regional contractor offering their customers total Mechanical, Electrical, & Plumbing preconstruction services, design-build/ design-assist and construction capabilities.  Their home office is in Metairie, LA.  They also have six satellite offices in:  Charlotte, High Point and Raleigh, NC; Memphis, TN; Long Beach, MS and Orlando, FL.  They have fabrication facilities in Kenner, LA; Memphis, TN; Long Beach, MS and High Point, NC.  They are licensed throughout the Southeastern US for both construction and engineering services.  The MCC Group has a diverse group of organizations as outlined below: Mechanical Construction Company, LLC is a commercial mechanical contractor performing work primarily in the New Orleans area.  They have performed many design-build/design-assist contracts, as well as high profile jobs such as the new VA Hospital and a large portion of the new University Medical Center.  These two projects are located in downtown New Orleans, cover 3.5 million square feet and stretch over 20 city blocks.   Mechanical Construction Company also contains a division called MCC Specialty Contractors which concentrates on smaller or specialized projects (i.e., tenant build out, computer rooms, chiller change outs). MCC Mechanical, LLC is a regional commercial mechanical contractor with offices in Memphis, TN; Long Beach, MS and Orlando, FL.  They have completed various mechanical projects across the Southeast.  Some projects include St. Jude Children’s Research Hospital in Memphis, multiple projects for Disney in the Orlando area and casino/hotel projects from Fort Lauderdale, FL to Durant, OK. MCC Mechanical of the Carolinas, LLC is a regional, commercial mechanical contractor with offices in Charlotte, High Point and Raleigh, NC.  They were a part of many high-rise projects such as the NASCAR Office Tower and Hearst Tower in Charlotte, which includes the world’s largest trading floor.  They also recently completed the Wake Forest University Baptist Memorial Hospital Cancer Center Expansion. Metal Construction Company, LLC is a sheet metal/ductwork fabricator and installation contractor with a fully mechanized fabrication facility located in Long Beach, MS.  Metal Construction compliments their mechanical divisions. MCC Services, LLC is a HVAC service and maintenance company, operating 15 trucks in the New Orleans and Gulf Coast areas.  MCC Services offers preventive maintenance contracts and also performs service and repairs.  Trison Interiors is a division of MCC Services providing metal stud, drywall and interior finish work.       MCC Electric, LLC is a regional commercial electrical contractor.  Preconstruction services parallel that of the mechanical businesses.  MCC Electric is licensed in various states and has performed work in much of those areas outlined in the Mechanical Construction Company and MCC Mechanical sections, above.

Description: Legal Sea Foods is an American restaurant chain of upscale casual-dining seafood restaurants.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Legal Sea Foods was born in 1950 when George Berkowitz opened a fish market in the Inman Square neighborhood of Cambridge, Massachusetts.  He opened it adjacent to his father Harry’s grocery store Legal Cash Market where customers were given “Legal Stamps” (forerunners of S&H green stamps) with their purchases.  It’s here that the “Legal” name became synonymous with quality and freshness.   In 1968, the Berkowitz family opened its first seafood restaurant, right next to the fish market.  The fish was simply prepared, either broiled or fried, and served on paper plates at communal picnic tables.  Despite the low-key trappings, the food was second to none and word quickly spread.  This early success led to further expansion and now, six decades later with restaurants along the Eastern Seaboard, the family philosophy endures: Legal Sea Foods is a fish company in the restaurant business.

Full Description: If you want to love where you live, visit Apex Manayunk today to view property photos, schedule a tour, or contact us for leasing information! Consider the favorite things you desire in an apartment home, and that's what Apex strives to deliver. A quiet residential community located in a vibrant neighborhood, with modern lifestyle amenities to make anyone feel instantly at home. Nestled along the Schuylkill River banks and Barmouth Trailhead but less than 10 miles from downtown Philadelphia, PA, Apex Manayunk offers residents a natural escape and an urban outlet. The Manayunk Community The Manayunk area was intentionally designed to promote an inclusive yet trendy lifestyle, the perfect fit for a modern generation. The neighborhood is an eclectic combination of students, young professionals, retirees, and new families looking for a community of like-minded neighbors to participate in engaging social events and cultural programs. The Manayunk community has a small-town vibe, hilly streets lined with Victorian architecture adjacent to modern lofts, and quaint row houses. Bikers enjoy the challenge of climbing the steep incline of "The Manayunk Wall" in an annual bike race, while shoppers can casually stroll among charming boutiques and galleries that line Main Street. Why choose us Quality Lifestyle At Apex, we know our tenants value health and wellness. That's why we added millions of dollars in renovations, including a state-of-the-art fitness center that overlooks the Manayunk Canal. Visit our exciting game room where neighbors enjoy using our billiards table and shuffle-board or challenging each other's skills with 5 NEW GAMES FOR GAME NIGHT. Our outdoor courtyard area is a great place to sit and chat while enjoying the fresh breeze that flows across the river banks. Or, you would instead enjoy an invigorating jog on our paved walking/running trail outside your door. We feature on-site bike storage, so our tenants never have to worry about hauling their bikes in and out of their units. Finally, our BBQ and deck area is perfect for sunning and enjoying an outdoor meal. You and your visitors might like to sip warm beverages and enjoy the glorious fall foliage surrounding Apex Manayunk. At Apex, our goal has always been to promote a quality lifestyle that enhances our tenant's health and well-being. Modern Amenities Private, gated parking Front desk attendant Upgraded lofts and townhomes (1 to 3 bedrooms) Gourmet kitchens with Stainless Steel Appliances Granite countertops and breakfast bar seating 9-foot ceilings with large windowed walls Huge walk-in closets with ample storage Upgraded hardwood floors throughout Marble master baths, some with deep linen storage Vivint Smart Home Features in select units Alexa or Google Home capable in all apartments Pet-friendly living with an on-site bark park Bocce ball field, BBQ area, and sun deck State-of-the-art fitness center An Arcade Game Room and Ping Pong Nearby Attractions Apex Manayunk is located in Montgomery County, PA., also known as the Valley Forge tourism area inside of Philadelphia - one of the few cities with major league teams in 5 professional franchises. At Apex, you're less than 10 minutes away from cheering on the Philadelphia Eagles, the Philadelphia Phillies, or the Philadelphia 76ers. The area is full of nearby, fun family attractions like Elmwood Park Zoo, where visitors can hand-feed towering, majestic giraffes and bison. And there are plenty of golf courses, quality restaurants, entertainment, and a calendar full of monthly community events. Enjoy a day's visit to historical sites.

Description: Hausfeld LLP is a leading global law firm that clients trust with their most complex legal disputes.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Hausfeld LLP is a preeminent international law firm that offers expert prosecution of complex legal disputes for a host of clients, both domestically and globally, in practice areas spanning antitrust/competition law, human and civil rights, environmental threats, consumer protection, securities fraud, and mass torts.  Hausfeld LLP's clients range from individuals to Fortune 500 businesses and organizations. With offices in Washington, D.C, San Francisco, London and affiliated offices through Europe, Asia, Latin America, Canada, Africa, and Australia, Hausfeld LLP is able to provide clients an international reach that allows its attorneys to solve difficult legal disputes across multiple jurisdictions and pursue claims on behalf of clients worldwide. Hausfeld LLP works closely with its clients to ensure exceptional results while always addressing any business sensitivities. Hausfeld LLP lawyers do so by anticipating issues, recognizing innovative strategies, and resolving legal disputes in a way that generates enduring benefits to stakeholders. Ingenuity and creativity are the hallmark of Hausfeld attorneys, which in turn attracts a broad range of clients from all fields and parts of the globe. Hausfeld LLP has represented multinational companies, small- and medium-sized companies, municipalities, pension funds, musicians, professional athletes, and individuals. Additionally, a firm-wide passion for furthering social justice has allowed it to serve a wide range of clients including Native Alaskans, Holocaust survivors, and South African apartheid victims.  This diverse roster of clients is representative of Hausfeld LLP’s broad expertise.  The law firm also utilizes its knowledge and experience to change and make law, generating admiration and accolades from some of the nation’s top federal judges. Since 2008, America’s federal judges have trusted Hausfeld LLP to be lead or co-lead counsel over 30 times in the some of most complex and challenging class cases brought in American courts. Globally, hundreds of clients have chosen Hausfeld LLP because of its proven track record of success here and abroad. Hausfeld LLP’s exceptional international reach, coupled with its unique and innovative strategies, enables the law firm to resolve complex legal problems.  Hausfeld is at the forefront of the law, overcoming jurisdictional, legal, and cultural obstacles to purse and achieve recoveries worldwide for its clients and for the classes and groups of claimants the law firm represents.  Hausfeld attorneys have a wide variety of skills and tools at their disposal to ensure its clients reach a successful resolution, whether inside the courtroom or privately in a conference room. More importantly, Hausfeld lawyers have proven their ability to deliver results when up against some of the largest law firms in the world. Hausfeld attorneys are known for their litigation acumen, and their ability to try cases when pre-trial resolution is not possible.  Hausfeld LLP was founded by Michael D. Hausfeld, who is widely respected as one of the nation’s top civil litigators and a leading expert in the fields of private antitrust/competition enforcement and international human rights. Under his leadership, Hausfeld LLP has become a leader in the legal field, a firm with a very bright future in the years ahead.
